^[chapter/01/sections][
  s01: {
    handle: "section/01"
    type: "section"
    title: "The Warm Furrow"
    excerpt: "Dawn smelled like frost and wet fur, and then—wrong, and lovely, and impossible—like hot iron. In the dawnward field the boonberries slept under a skin of ice, each one holding its drop of light banked low against the..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s01]{open}
  }
  s02: <
    handle: "custom-boof/02"
    type: "custom-boof"
    valence: "boon"
    excerpt: "For as long as she had carried a name, Boof had worked for the land and not for anyone who owned a piece of it. She knew the dawnward field by scent the way other creatures knew it by map: which vine had been generous..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s02]{open}
  >
  s03: {
    handle: "section/03"
    type: "section"
    title: "When a Berry Listens"
    excerpt: "Most boonberries sleep through everything. They are fruit, lantern-fuel, seed, and supper—ordinary magic, the kind a town spends without naming. But now and then a berry notices the shape of the story it is sitting in..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s03]{open}
  }
  s04: [
    handle: "figure/04"
    type: "figure"
    image: "/seeds/2026-03-01/spwashi_lore.land_hero_ab096673-48d1-42cc-806e-88f43001c127.webp"
    route: ^[chapter/01/s04]{open}
  ]
  s05: {
    handle: "section/05"
    type: "section"
    title: "The Maps That Look Away"
    excerpt: "By full morning Boof had carried the egg—warm as a loaf, heavier than a loaf, and getting warmer—up the slope to the map-house, where Boon.land keeps its record of everything it has agreed to say exists. She had thoug..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s05]{open}
  }
  s06: {
    handle: "section/06"
    type: "section"
    title: "Following the Heat"
    excerpt: "There is a kind of problem a map cannot help you with, and Boof had just met the largest one of her life. If no record would hold the egg, then the egg was not a thing to be filed. It was a thing to be followed. She t..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s06]{open}
  }
  s07: <
    handle: "custom-boof/07"
    type: "custom-boof"
    excerpt: "By the time the light went level and amber, Boof was a long way from any desk she had ever been offered and did not miss a single one of them. She had a warm egg no map would name, a direction the field had chosen for..."
    route: ^[chapter/01/s07]{open}
  >
]

