#[chapter/01/lore]{
  notes: [
    "Boof is a dog based on Spwashi's dog. She works for the land, not an owner—paid in blueberries, honest scents, and trails that end in something real."
    "Boonberry light is shared warmth: stoves, lanterns, winter kitchens. It sleeps until something the world has no word for asks it to pay attention."
    "The egg—warm, unclaimed, unhatched—arrives on a road that does not exist yet. Its heat may be a countdown, an invitation, or a debt. The story does not yet say which."
    "Boon.land's records hold only what the world has agreed exists. Ink will not take the egg's name; the maps end where its heat begins."
    "The field chooses a direction before the people do—the berries lean toward the grove, off the edge of every known route."
    "A hairline crack shaped like a door opens along the egg's crown as it warms. Something inside is keeping time."
    "The grove downhill keeps echoes and will not be named after dark; Boof carries the egg toward it. (Chamber 02.)"
    "Dregg: dragon's egg—the dregs that settle to the bottom of a season and are still warm to the touch."
  ]
}

